      "share": {
        "link": "https://www.instagram.com/reel/DS0qqxFDjh4/?id=3797848042649827448_30146655186",
        "share_text": "Only an uncle would give toddlers a foot-and-a-half long live lizard for Christmas.\u00f0\u009f\u00a4\u00a6\u00e2\u0080\u008d\u00e2\u0099\u0080\u00ef\u00b8\u008f\u00f0\u009f\u00a4\u00a6\u00e2\u0080\u008d\u00e2\u0099\u0080\u00ef\u00b8\u008f\u00f0\u009f\u00a4\u00a6\u00e2\u0080\u008d\u00e2\u0099\u0080\u00ef\u00b8\u008f\u00f0\u009f\u0098\u0085\u00f0\u009f\u0098\u0085\u00f0\u009f\u0098\u0085 Welcome to the family Peter.  #bestuncleintheworld #beardeddragonlove\n\nSidenote: Uncle Hazen talked to me and their mama about this ahead of time. He is keeping the lizard here and caring for him. He has a beautiful set up and is well cared for. We had a bearded dragon for many years when my kids were little and are well aware on how to take care of them properly. We live on a farm and care for over 100 animals here daily. I have had some VERY rude messages as if we are going to keep Peter as a Christmas gift for a week and then let him starve to death. \u00f0\u009f\u00a4\u00a6\u00e2\u0080\u008d\u00e2\u0099\u0080\u00ef\u00b8\u008f\u00f0\u009f\u0099\u0084 Peter is actually almost 10 years old and needed a home. Hazen thought it would be a really fun first reptile pet for the boys because he is SO chill. They love reptiles and have already become great friends! Peter will live out the rest of his days here in a loving home, well cared for, and with lots of love and attention. No need to assume the worst just because he happened to give him to his nephews as a fun Christmas present. We are all very much aware of the commitment a new pet requires. If you have followed us for any period of time, you know that we care for any animal that comes in our path and that we are capable and committed.",
